According to a poll commissioned by Express Employment Professionals, the majority of blue-collar workers in the U.S. are optimistic about the direction of their lives. The survey found that 85% of blue-collar workers feel that their lives are headed in the right direction, and 86% are satisfied with their jobs. Additionally, 69% of those surveyed said they are happy with the direction of their local communities, and 51% feel the same about the direction of the country as a whole. Furthermore, 55% of the workers said they are better off now than they were five years ago.